This paper belongs to the field of educational data mining, which is a subfield of computer science that focuses on analyzing educational data to improve the learning process. The paper specifically looks at academic indicators within a virtual learning environment, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), machine learning (cs.LG), computer engineering (cs.CE), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
